The Research Landscape of Rural Sustainable Livelihood: A Scientometric Analysis
A. Hasyim Asyari Amir Husni, Muhammad Chaeroel Ansar, Kuntala Chowdhury, Muhammad Chaeroel Ansar 
This study uses a scientometric approach — analysing 1,141 articles from 1988 to 2023 — to map the intellectual landscape of rural sustainable livelihoods. It traces how the field evolved through four phases: preparation, initial growth, rapid expansion, and stabilization. Key themes include climate change adaptation, sustainable livelihood frameworks, and social capital. China, India, and South Africa emerged as leading contributors. 
The paper also identifies critical gaps: author and institutional collaboration networks remain fragmented, and themes like gender equality and digital innovation in rural development are underexplored.
